<Link id="l00263" /><CodeLine lineNumber="263"><Highlight kind="comment">/// ChainedFixupTarget holds all the information about an external symbol</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00264" /><CodeLine lineNumber="264"><Highlight kind="comment">/// necessary to bind this binary to that symbol. These values are referenced</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00265" /><CodeLine lineNumber="265"><Highlight kind="comment">/// indirectly by chained fixup binds. This structure captures values from all</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00266" /><CodeLine lineNumber="266"><Highlight kind="comment">/// import and symbol formats.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00267" /><CodeLine lineNumber="267"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00268" /><CodeLine lineNumber="268"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Be aware there are two notions of weak here:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00269" /><CodeLine lineNumber="269"><Highlight kind="comment">///   WeakImport == true</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00270" /><CodeLine lineNumber="270"><Highlight kind="comment">///     The associated bind may be set to 0 if this symbol is missing from its</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00271" /><CodeLine lineNumber="271"><Highlight kind="comment">///     parent library. This is called a &quot;weak import.&quot;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00272" /><CodeLine lineNumber="272"><Highlight kind="comment">///   LibOrdinal == BIND&#95;SPECIAL&#95;DYLIB&#95;WEAK&#95;LOOKUP</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00273" /><CodeLine lineNumber="273"><Highlight kind="comment">///     This symbol may be coalesced with other libraries vending the same</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00274" /><CodeLine lineNumber="274"><Highlight kind="comment">///     symbol. E.g., C++&#39;s &quot;operator new&quot;. This is called a &quot;weak bind.&quot;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00312" /><CodeLine lineNumber="312"><Highlight kind="comment">/// MachOAbstractFixupEntry is an abstract class representing a fixup in a</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00313" /><CodeLine lineNumber="313"><Highlight kind="comment">/// MH&#95;DYLDLINK file. Fixups generally represent rebases and binds. Binds also</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00314" /><CodeLine lineNumber="314"><Highlight kind="comment">/// subdivide into additional subtypes (weak, lazy, reexport).</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00315" /><CodeLine lineNumber="315"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00316" /><CodeLine lineNumber="316"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The two concrete subclasses of MachOAbstractFixupEntry are:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00317" /><CodeLine lineNumber="317"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00318" /><CodeLine lineNumber="318"><Highlight kind="comment">///   MachORebaseBindEntry   - for dyld opcode-based tables, including threaded-</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00319" /><CodeLine lineNumber="319"><Highlight kind="comment">///                            rebase, where rebases are mixed in with other</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00320" /><CodeLine lineNumber="320"><Highlight kind="comment">///                            bind opcodes.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00321" /><CodeLine lineNumber="321"><Highlight kind="comment">///   MachOChainedFixupEntry - for pointer chains embedded in data pages.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
